# 15. 寂しいなぁ、って

Mizuki: It's already 25:00?
Mizuki: Everyone was really on edge last night. I hope we can have a little more fun today.
Mizuki: <Hey there! Everyone ready to get some work done?! Huh? Is it just you, Enanan? Where's K?>
Ena: <She's not here. She's been AFK all day.>
Mizuki: <What? She hasn't overdone it already, has she?>
Ena: <I don't know. I sent a DM, but she never responded.>
Mizuki: <I hope everything's okay. I knew her taking on everything like that would be too much. Without Yuki...>
Ena: <..... We don't need Yuki.>
Mizuki: <Come on, Enanan. You're not still angry, are you? If you keep frowning like that, you're going to end up with wrinkles.>
Ena: <I'm not angry. I'm just saying that Yuki has no reason to be part of N25 anymore.>
Ena: <If she can make such great songs on her own, then why wouldn't she?>
Mizuki: <That may be true, but still...>
Mizuki: (Enanan's acting strangely too.)
Mizuki: (I guess I can't say I'm feeling all that great either, though. Everyone's worried about something.)
Mizuki: (I'm sure even K and Enanan are the same way.)
???: Be honest, K, Enanan, Amia... You all want to disappear more than anyone.
Mizuki: <.....>
Mizuki: <I bet Yuki's been struggling for a while now, too.>
Ena: <What?>
Mizuki: <The day Yuki disappeared, I overheard her and her mom talking.>
Mizuki: <Her mom seemed like the kind of person who tends to push their own sense of values on others. Yuki brushed it off, saying that it doesn't really bother her.>
Mizuki: <I figured it wouldn't be a problem if she was fine with things, but you saw the way she was acting in that place.>
Mizuki: <It made me think maybe Yuki was trying to please her mom by going along with whatever she thought was best.>
Ena: <.....>
Mizuki: <It's probably not just her mom, either.>
Mizuki: <Maybe Yuki has been changing herself to fit in with the expectations of everyone around her.>
Mizuki: <Maybe she thought she had to always be a “good girl”, never inconveniencing others in order for them to like her.>
Mizuki: <And now it's finally become too much to handle and she doesn't know what to do anymore. At least, that's the feeling I get.>
Ena: <.....>
Mizuki: <I'm not saying I'm perfect or anything.>
Mizuki: <But I think I understand how she feels. I know how suffocating it can be always feeling pressured to fit into other people's expectations of you.>
Ena: <I didn't realize you felt that way too.>
Mizuki: <Yeah, well...>
Mizuki: <Hey, wait a minute! What do you mean by that?! Even I have stuff to deal with, you know!>
Ena: <Oh, sorry. It's just that you always sound so carefree. Like you're always having fun.>
Mizuki: <Oh, well you've gotta enjoy life while you can, right?>
Mizuki: <It's no fun being negative all the time! Don't you want to live every day to its fullest, Enanan?♪>
Ena: <Well, sure. I want to enjoy myself.>
Mizuki: <I think Yuki just wasn't able to do that, though.>
Mizuki: <I bet she's been struggling alone for so long that she just reached her breaking point.>
Ena: <.....>
Mizuki: <If Yuki really did end up like this from being in so much pain, and now feels like she just wants to disappear...>
Mizuki: <I just think that sounds kinda sad.>
Ena: <.....>
Mizuki: <I'd like to try talking to her again.>
Mizuki: <We can go back by playing that “Untitled” song, right? If that's true...>
Ena: <That's what Miku said. But will talking to Yuki in her current state of mind achieve anything?>
Ena: <What was that?>
Mizuki: <Oh! It's a notification about OWN. Yuki uploaded a new song!>
Ena: <Another one? She just released one not too long ago.>
Mizuki: <What? Two songs in a row? Wait, now it's three?>
Ena: <How many is she making? What kind of songs are they?>
Ena: <What the hell? They're even darker than before.>
Mizuki: <Whoa! I'm getting shivers!>
Ena: <This isn't good. I can't put it into words, but I have a bad feeling about this...>
???: But if I can't find myself even then...then I'll just have to disappear.
Ena: <Was she serious?>
Kanade: <Enanan. Amia.>
Ena & Mizuki: <K!>
